China Railway, China Southern, MTR: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-05-19T00:48:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/china-railway-china-southern-mtr-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 0.5 percent to 23,011.14. The Hang
Seng China Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, gained 1.1 percent to 12,870.83.  China Railway Construction Corp. (1186 HK): China Railway,
the builder of more than half the nation’s railroads, set up a
company in Beijing yesterday with total investment of 3 billion
yuan ($461 million), according to Xinhua News Agency. The stock
gained 1 percent to HK$6.85.  China Southern Airlines Co. (1055 HK): Parent China
Southern Air Holding Co. signed an accord with the government of
Beijing’s Daxing district for a hub at the new airport being
built there, Shanghai Daily reported. China Southern Airlines,
 Asia ’s largest carrier by passenger numbers, rose 1.1 percent to
HK$4.51.  MTR Corp. (66)  (66 HK): Hong Kong government awarded the city’s
subway operator two plots of land to offset the railway
operator’s HK$17.7 billion ($2.28 billion) construction cost for
two rail lines, Eva Cheng, secretary for transport and housing,
said. The stock advanced 0.4 percent to HK$28.05.  PetroChina Co. (857 HK): The country’s biggest energy
company plans to double the value of its global oil and gas
trading business in 2015 through a network of new offices in  New
York ,  London  and  Singapore , Chairman Jiang Jiemin said. The
shares rose 1 percent to HK$10.58.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Nick Gentle at
   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 